Course Title: Azure Architect Technologies
Course Description:
This course is designed to teach students the fundamentals of Azure Architect Technologies, including designing and implementing solutions that run on Microsoft Azure, as well as managing and monitoring those solutions. The course is intended for IT professionals who have some experience with Azure and want to advance their skills and knowledge in designing, implementing and managing complex cloud-based solutions.
Course Outline:
Module 1: Introduction to Azure Architect Technologies
* Overview of Azure Architect Technologies
* Benefits of using Azure for Architecting Solutions
* Azure Resource Manager and Azure Marketplace
* Azure services for architecting solutions
Module 2: Azure Infrastructure Services
* Virtual Machines, Virtual Networks and Load Balancers
* Azure App Services, Containers and Kubernetes Services
* Storage Accounts and Azure Files
* Azure Database Services
Module 3: Azure Security and Identity Services
* Azure Active Directory
* Multi-Factor Authentication and Conditional Access Policies
* Role-Based Access Control and Azure Policy
* Azure Security Center
Module 4: Azure Integration and Monitoring Services
* Azure Integration Services: Logic Apps, API Management and Service Bus
* Azure Monitoring Services: Azure Monitor, Application Insights and Log Analytics
* Azure Event Grid and Azure Event Hub
* Azure Backup and Azure Site Recovery
Module 5: Azure Architecture Design and Best Practices
* Designing highly available and scalable solutions
* Implementing Disaster Recovery and Business Continuity plans
* Hybrid Cloud Architectures and Azure Migration Services
* Best Practices for Azure Security and Compliance
Learning Outcome:
By the end of the course, the students will have gained an in-depth understanding of Azure Architect Technologies and be able to design, implement and manage complex cloud-based solutions on Microsoft Azure. The students will also have the knowledge to implement best practices for Azure Security and Compliance.
Prerequisites:
The students should have some experience with Microsoft Azure and should have a basic understanding of cloud computing concepts. The students should also have a good understanding of networking, security and operating systems.

